"east of Edgware with a stream called Edgware Brook, which has its sources upon the southern slopes of Stanmore, and takes partly a southern, partly an eastern course, till it passes under the Edgware Road to the confluence just mentioned. These combined brooks form the Silk Stream, which follows a nearly southward course, till, after receiving a tributary that drains the south-western slope of Mill Hill, it combines its waters with those of Dollis Brook in the broad expanse of Hendon Reservoir."